','closed','','1428-revision-v1','','','2017-05-16 12:16:39','2017-05-16 12:16:39','',1428,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/2017/05/16/1428-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1430,1,'2017-05-16 12:17:19','2017-05-16 12:17:19',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','1430','','','2017-05-16 12:17:19','2017-05-16 12:17:19','',0,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/?p=1430',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(1431,1,'2017-05-16 12:17:19','2017-05-16 12:17:19',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','1431','','','2017-05-16 12:17:19','2017-05-16 12:17:19','',0,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/?p=1431',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(1432,5,'2017-01-20 12:00:13','2017-01-20 12:00:13','<p>I was recently asked what are the common characteristics of a winning bot – and after some deliberation, my core answer is pretty much the same it would be for any winning business. &nbsp;I broke it down as a top 7:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>“Can’t touch this” – know who you can reach. &nbsp;Choose a narrow audience who you can effective reach.</li>\r\n<li>Greatest pain / want – you can effectively diagnose what’s really impacting this audience. &nbsp;What keeps them up at night?</li>\r\n<li>Invent something new that addresses the need in a novel, whole new way.</li>\r\n<li>In bot world, to me that is the conversational UI. &nbsp;What is the personality of the bot? &nbsp;How do you efficiently use language and cognitive process to lead the user to best outcomes. &nbsp;This is where you differentiate in a sustainable way.</li>\r\n<li>Figure out how to scale to cost efficiently</li>\r\n<li>Again in bot world, this would mean taking your bot and deploying it as far and wide as possible. &nbsp;This means working across ALL the networks. &nbsp;Limiting yourself to a single network, or small number, greatly impacts your reach.</li>\r\n<li>Can’t let the frosting make the cake. &nbsp;Stary eyes on Snapchat, or button dialogs on Messenger should not be core conversational UI decision points. &nbsp;You can enhance the delivery of final content, but not alter the flow of the conversation. &nbsp;As soon as you start letting the creative of a channel dictate the conversational UI you will end up building numerous discreet bots.\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>And to preemptively strike on the notion that a custom built bot to channel would be better – I’d counter you’d give up a lot of training benefit by missing the additional data and consistent structure. &nbsp;So while it could be slightly prettier, it would be a lot dumber.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>And here are some enlightened slides to back the points!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1pk1xYpJaHE92TaIIdmdSCzHEvqpMYFnE1hJbfB_Fzec/edit#slide=id.p\"><img src=\"https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Winning-Bot-Strategies-300x169.png\"></a></p>','Winning Bot Strategies','','publish','open','open','','winning-bot-strategies','','','2017-05-31 11:03:16','2017-05-31 11:03:16','',0,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/?p=1432',0,'post','',0),(1433,1,'2017-05-17 11:59:23','2017-05-17 11:59:23','','mchammer2','','inherit','open','closed','','mchammer2','','','2017-05-17 11:59:23','2017-05-17 11:59:23','',1432,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/mchammer2.gif',0,'attachment','image/gif',0),(1434,1,'2017-05-17 12:00:13','2017-05-17 12:00:13','<p>I was recently asked what are the common characteristics of a winning bot – and after some deliberation, my core answer is pretty much the same it would be for any winning business. &nbsp;I broke it down as a top 7:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>“Can’t touch this” – know who you can reach. &nbsp;Choose a narrow audience who you can effective reach.</li>\r\n<li>Greatest pain / want – you can effectively diagnose what’s really impacting this audience. &nbsp;What keeps them up at night?</li>\r\n<li>Invent something new that addresses the need in a novel, whole new way.</li>\r\n<li>In bot world, to me that is the conversational UI. &nbsp;What is the personality of the bot? &nbsp;How do you efficiently use language and cognitive process to lead the user to best outcomes. &nbsp;This is where you differentiate in a sustainable way.</li>\r\n<li>Figure out how to scale to cost efficiently</li>\r\n<li>Again in bot world, this would mean taking your bot and deploying it as far and wide as possible. &nbsp;This means working across ALL the networks. &nbsp;Limiting yourself to a single network, or small number, greatly impacts your reach.</li>\r\n<li>Can’t let the frosting make the cake. &nbsp;Stary eyes on Snapchat, or button dialogs on Messenger should not be core conversational UI decision points. &nbsp;You can enhance the delivery of final content, but not alter the flow of the conversation. &nbsp;As soon as you start letting the creative of a channel dictate the conversational UI you will end up building numerous discreet bots.\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>And to preemptively strike on the notion that a custom built bot to channel would be better – I’d counter you’d give up a lot of training benefit by missing the additional data and consistent structure. &nbsp;So while it could be slightly prettier, it would be a lot dumber.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>And here are some enlightened slides to back the points!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1pk1xYpJaHE92TaIIdmdSCzHEvqpMYFnE1hJbfB_Fzec/edit#slide=id.p\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-6689\" src=\"https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Winning-Bot-Strategies-300x169.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"288\" height=\"162\" srcset=\"https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Winning-Bot-Strategies-300x169.png 300w, https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Winning-Bot-Strategies-768x434.png 768w, https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Winning-Bot-Strategies-800x450.png 800w, https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Winning-Bot-Strategies-75x42.png 75w, https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/Winning-Bot-Strategies.png 809w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 288px) 100vw, 288px\"></a></p>','Winning Bot Strategies','','inherit','closed','closed','','1432-revision-v1','','','2017-05-17 12:00:13','2017-05-17 12:00:13','',1432,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/2017/05/17/1432-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1435,5,'2017-01-16 12:03:36','2017-01-16 12:03:36','<a href=\"http://www.massively.ai/\">Massively</a>, makers of an AI bot framework, released a tongue-in-cheek Spotify plugin this past summer that brings sage Vulcan wisdom to the table in form of “<a href=\"https://join.skype.com/bot/7fa82ae6-547c-41b1-ba00-9de3b4190dac?add\">Spock</a>“. &nbsp;Biggest issue… is Spock permanently offline? &nbsp;Is there some plot twist at play here?','Spock spotted on Skype','','publish','open','open','','spock-spotted-on-skype','','','2017-05-31 11:03:35','2017-05-31 11:03:35','',0,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/?p=1435',0,'post','',0),(1436,1,'2017-05-17 12:02:59','2017-05-17 12:02:59','','mr-spock-mr-spock-10874060-1036-730','','inherit','open','closed','','mr-spock-mr-spock-10874060-1036-730','','','2017-05-17 12:02:59','2017-05-17 12:02:59','',1435,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/mr-spock-mr-spock-10874060-1036-730.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1437,1,'2017-05-17 12:03:36','2017-05-17 12:03:36','<a href=\"http://www.massively.ai/\">Massively</a>, makers of an AI bot framework, released a tongue-in-cheek Spotify plugin this past summer that brings sage Vulcan wisdom to the table in form of “<a href=\"https://join.skype.com/bot/7fa82ae6-547c-41b1-ba00-9de3b4190dac?add\">Spock</a>“. &nbsp;Biggest issue… is Spock permanently offline? &nbsp;Is there some plot twist at play here?','Spock spotted on Skype','','inherit','closed','closed','','1435-revision-v1','','','2017-05-17 12:03:36','2017-05-17 12:03:36','',1435,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/2017/05/17/1435-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1438,5,'2017-01-16 12:01:24','2017-01-16 12:01:24','<p>Bots wouldn’t be nearly as interesting if it weren’t for the rise of conversant. &nbsp;Really, the bigger story is this rising sea change in how people engage w/ technology. &nbsp;This change is what makes bots so relevant and a critical path for brands to join the conversation.</p>\r\n<p><span id=\"more-6595\"></span></p>\r\n<p>So… what we mean by “conversant” is any channel through which voice is the primary UI. &nbsp;This isn’t all futuristic Star Trek stuff – conversant has already made large inroads. &nbsp;2016 the voice based digital assistants, principally Alexa, arrived on the scene in a big way. &nbsp;But this follows on the heels of explosive growth in messaging where the likes of SnapChat, Slack, Messenger, and a host of others have quickly grown to be the highest utilized channel. &nbsp;And while today, lesser known, there is also a push towards direct to brand communications via SMS, on-site tool, etc.</p>\r\n<p><iframe width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/hShY6xZWVGE?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p>The notion of conversant interfaces is not new. &nbsp;What is though now, from a services standpoint, is how much better they’ve gotten at delivering an efficient experience. &nbsp;Also, where in the past network providers took a very closed garden approach, now folks have wised up and are driving lots of innovation from independent publishers.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1B6zp9VYN2C7apYrfp7slEPIzNUyEbACD-bAVzlYlJ-E/edit#slide=id.p\"><img src=\"https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rise-of-conversant.png\"></a></p>\r\n<p>This underpins our belief and role we want to play w/ BetterBots. &nbsp;Innovation is going to chiefly come from independent publishers trying and discovering new things. &nbsp;This is why we’ve organized so much content and resource that we are freely promoting separately from our efforts w/ uTu.ai.</p>','The Rise of Conversant','','publish','open','open','','the-rise-of-conversan