t, is how much better they’ve gotten at delivering an efficient experience. &nbsp;Also, where in the past network providers took a very closed garden approach, now folks have wised up and are driving lots of innovation from independent publishers.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1B6zp9VYN2C7apYrfp7slEPIzNUyEbACD-bAVzlYlJ-E/edit#slide=id.p\"><img src=\"https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rise-of-conversant.png\"></a></p>\r\n<p>This underpins our belief and role we want to play w/ BetterBots. &nbsp;Innovation is going to chiefly come from independent publishers trying and discovering new things. &nbsp;This is why we’ve organized so much content and resource that we are freely promoting separately from our efforts w/ uTu.ai.</p>','The Rise of Conversant','','inherit','closed','closed','','1438-revision-v1','','','2017-05-17 12:07:24','2017-05-17 12:07:24','',1438,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/2017/05/17/1438-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1442,6,'2017-01-14 12:09:39','2017-01-14 12:09:39','<p>At the end of 2016 Facebook rolled out some really nice reporting for activity on Messenger. &nbsp;For a serious bot maker, however, it’s a seriously flawed approach with some key gaps in coverage.</p>\r\n<p><span id=\"more-6554\"></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Always on. &nbsp;You don’t have to instrument anything and get insight on dialogs automatically.</li>\r\n<li>Provides some nice demographic detail on Facebook users.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Zero code integration also means you can’t track custom events. &nbsp;These are key to understanding much of the conversation flow.</li>\r\n<li>Walled garden perspective. &nbsp;This shows just Messenger activity and doesn’t account for engagements you have elsewhere.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>End story, its a place to get started, but once you getting serious about your bot, you’ll need more.</p>','So… What about Facebook Bot Analytics?','','publish','open','open','','so-what-about-facebook-bot-analytics','','','2017-05-31 11:04:56','2017-05-31 11:04:56','',0,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/?p=1442',0,'post','',0),(1443,1,'2017-05-17 12:09:26','2017-05-17 12:09:26','','Bots-for-Mess','','inherit','open','closed','','bots-for-mess','','','2017-05-17 12:09:26','2017-05-17 12:09:26','',1442,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Bots-for-Mess.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1444,1,'2017-05-17 12:09:39','2017-05-17 12:09:39','<p>At the end of 2016 Facebook rolled out some really nice reporting for activity on Messenger. &nbsp;For a serious bot maker, however, it’s a seriously flawed approach with some key gaps in coverage.</p>\r\n<p><span id=\"more-6554\"></span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://developers.facebook.com/docs/messenger-platform/product-overview/analytics\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-7618\" src=\"https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/facebook-analy-300x169.png\" width=\"424\" height=\"239\"></a></p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Always on. &nbsp;You don’t have to instrument anything and get insight on dialogs automatically.</li>\r\n<li>Provides some nice demographic detail on Facebook users.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Zero code integration also means you can’t track custom events. &nbsp;These are key to understanding much of the conversation flow.</li>\r\n<li>Walled garden perspective. &nbsp;This shows just Messenger activity and doesn’t account for engagements you have elsewhere.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>End story, its a place to get started, but once you getting serious about your bot, you’ll need more.</p>','So… What about Facebook Bot Analytics?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1442-revision-v1','','','2017-05-17 12:09:39','2017-05-17 12:09:39','',1442,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/2017/05/17/1442-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1445,1,'2017-05-17 12:17:39','2017-05-17 12:17:39','<p>At the end of 2016 Facebook rolled out some really nice reporting for activity on Messenger. &nbsp;For a serious bot maker, however, it’s a seriously flawed approach with some key gaps in coverage.</p>\r\n<p><span id=\"more-6554\"></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Pros:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Always on. &nbsp;You don’t have to instrument anything and get insight on dialogs automatically.</li>\r\n<li>Provides some nice demographic detail on Facebook users.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Cons:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Zero code integration also means you can’t track custom events. &nbsp;These are key to understanding much of the conversation flow.</li>\r\n<li>Walled garden perspective. &nbsp;This shows just Messenger activity and doesn’t account for engagements you have elsewhere.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>End story, its a place to get started, but once you getting serious about your bot, you’ll need more.</p>','So… What about Facebook Bot Analytics?','','inherit','closed','closed','','1442-revision-v1','','','2017-05-17 12:17:39','2017-05-17 12:17:39','',1442,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/2017/05/17/1442-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1447,6,'2017-01-14 12:20:41','2017-01-14 12:20:41','<p>When working w/ bots and all the extended channels and platforms that need to exchange data with its very helpful to be able to work from local instance. We love <a href=\"https://github.com/localtunnel/localtunnel\">localtunnel.me</a> but find that its popularity hurts its stability. For use w/ our classes therefore we’ve enabled a free, private’sh localtunnel which can be accessed at https://www.bot-tunnel.com/.</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>','Free bot-tunnel','','publish','open','open','','free-bot-tunnel','','','2017-05-31 11:04:26','2017-05-31 11:04:26','',0,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/?p=1447',0,'post','',0),(1448,1,'2017-05-17 12:20:12','2017-05-17 12:20:12','','penguin','','inherit','open','closed','','penguin','','','2017-05-17 12:20:12','2017-05-17 12:20:12','',1447,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/penguin.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1449,1,'2017-05-17 12:20:41','2017-05-17 12:20:41','<p>When working w/ bots and all the extended channels and platforms that need to exchange data with its very helpful to be able to work from local instance. We love <a href=\"https://github.com/localtunnel/localtunnel\">localtunnel.me</a> but find that its popularity hurts its stability. For use w/ our classes therefore we’ve enabled a free, private’sh localtunnel which can be accessed at https://www.bot-tunnel.com/.</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>','Free bot-tunnel','','inherit','closed','closed','','1447-revision-v1','','','2017-05-17 12:20:41','2017-05-17 12:20:41','',1447,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/2017/05/17/1447-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1452,1,'2017-05-17 12:36:46','2017-05-17 12:36:46','','rise-of-conversant','','inherit','open','closed','','rise-of-conversant-2','','','2017-05-17 12:36:46','2017-05-17 12:36:46','',0,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/rise-of-conversant-1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1453,1,'2017-05-17 12:36:52','2017-05-17 12:36:52','<p>I was recently asked what are the common characteristics of a winning bot – and after some deliberation, my core answer is pretty much the same it would be for any winning business. &nbsp;I broke it down as a top 7:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>“Can’t touch this” – know who you can reach. &nbsp;Choose a narrow audience who you can effective reach.</li>\n<li>Greatest pain / want – you can effectively diagnose what’s really impacting this audience. &nbsp;What keeps them up at night?</li>\n<li>Invent something new that addresses the need in a novel, whole new way.</li>\n<li>In bot world, to me that is the conversational UI. &nbsp;What is the personality of the bot? &nbsp;How do you efficiently use language and cognitive process to lead the user to best outcomes. &nbsp;This is where you differentiate in a sustainable way.</li>\n<li>Figure out how to scale to cost efficiently</li>\n<li>Again in bot world, this would mean taking your bot and deploying it as far and wide as possible. &nbsp;This means working across ALL the networks. &nbsp;Limiting yourself to a single network, or small number, greatly impacts your reach.</li>\n<li>Can’t let the frosting make the cake. &nbsp;Stary eyes on Snapchat, or button dialogs on Messenger should not be core conversational UI decision points. &nbsp;You can enhance the delivery of final content, but not alter the flow of the conversation. &nbsp;As soon as you start letting the creative of a channel dictate the conversational UI you will end up building numerous discreet bots.\n<ol>\n<li>And to preemptively strike on the notion that a custom built bot to channel would be better – I’d counter you’d give up a lot of training benefit by missing the additional data and consistent structure. &nbsp;So while it could be slightly prettier, it would be a lot dumber.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>And here are some enlightened slides to back the points!</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1pk1xYpJaHE92TaIIdmdSCzHEvqpMYFnE1hJbfB_Fzec/edit#slide=id.p\"><img src=\"\"></a></p>','Winning Bot Strategies','','inherit','closed','closed','','1432-autosave-v1','','','2017-05-17 12:36:52','2017-05-17 12:36:52','',1432,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/2017/05/17/1432-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1454,1,'2017-05-17 12:37:08','2017-05-17 12:37:08','','Winning-Bot-Strategies-300x169','','inherit','open','closed','','winning-bot-strategies-300x169','','','2017-05-17 12:37:08','2017-05-17 12:37:08','',0,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Winning-Bot-Strategies-300x169.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1455,1,'2017-05-17 12:37:21','2017-05-17 12:37:21','<p>I was recently asked what are the common characteristics of a winning bot – and after some deliberation, my core answer is pretty much the same it would be for any winning business. &nbsp;I broke it down as a top 7:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>“Can’t touch this” – know who you can reach. &nbsp;Choose a narrow audience who you can effective reach.</li>\r\n<li>Greatest pain / want – you can effectively diagnose what’s really impacting this audience. &nbsp;What keeps them up at night?</li>\r\n<li>Invent something new that addresses the need in a novel, whole new way.</li>\r\n<li>In bot world, to me that is the conversational UI. &nbsp;What is the personality of the bot? &nbsp;How do you efficiently use language and cognitive process to lead the user to best outcomes. &nbsp;This is where you differentiate in a sustainable way.</li>\r\n<li>Figure out how to scale to cost efficiently</li>\r\n<li>Again in bot world, this would mean taking your bot and deploying it as far and wide as possible. &nbsp;This means working across ALL the networks. &nbsp;Limiting yourself to a single network, or small number, greatly impacts your reach.</li>\r\n<li>Can’t let the frosting make the cake. &nbsp;Stary eyes on Snapchat, or button dialogs on Messenger should not be core conversational UI decision points. &nbsp;You can enhance the delivery of final content, but not alter the flow of the conversation. &nbsp;As soon as you start letting the creative of a channel dictate the conversational UI you will end up building numerous discreet bots.\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>And to preemptively strike on the notion that a custom built bot to channel would be better – I’d counter you’d give up a lot of training benefit by missing the additional data and consistent structure. &nbsp;So while it could be slightly prettier, it would be a lot dumber.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>And here are some enlightened slides to back the points!</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1pk1xYpJaHE92TaIIdmdSCzHEvqpMYFnE1hJbfB_Fzec/edit#slide=id.p\"><img src=\"https://betterbots.utu.ai/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Winning-Bot-Strategies-300x169.png\"></a></p>','Winning Bot Strategies','','inherit','closed','closed','','1432-revision-v1','','','2017-05-17 12:37:21','2017-05-17 12:37:21','',1432,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/2017/05/17/1432-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1456,1,'2017-03-06 12:35:24','2017-03-06 12:35:24','We would like to invite you to join us in our next Meetup about Alexa Bot!\r\n\r\nThis hands on session will cover the basics of creating a bot for Amazon Alexa. We will cover a potential development workflow, setup on Amazon, and instrumenting a production environment for further improvement. The Meetup will be directed by Jimmie Butler, a co-founder at Utu Intelligence, a company that is building a bot analytics platform, and working to help developers build better bots.\r\n\r\n<b>*Please be aware that the conference will be 100% in English.</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou should come to this session if you:\r\n\r\n• Want to learn how to build an Amazon Alexa powered bot\r\n\r\n• Want to learn common patterns used in building bots\r\n\r\n• Want to explore the possibilities of working with a conversational UI\r\n\r\n• Want to learn about the benefits of deploying your bot cross platforms\r\n\r\nAlso, come to the session with…\r\n\r\n• Comfort with JavaScript\r\n\r\n• Comfort with git and github\r\n\r\n• A laptop tricked out with your IDE of choice\r\n\r\nWe hope to see you there!\r\n\r\nhttps://www.meetup.com/medellin-java/events/238155228','Medellin – My First Bot in 90min','','publish','open','open','','medellin-my-first-bot-in-90min','','','2017-05-31 13:18:50','2017-05-31 13:18:50','',0,'https://betterbots.utu.ai/?p=1456',0,'post','',0),(1457,1,'2017-05-17 12:42:24','2017-05-17 12:42:24','<p>We would like to invite you to join us in our next Meetup about Alexa Bot!</p>\r\n<p>This hands on session will cover the basics of creating a bot for Amazon Alexa. We will cover a potential development workflow, setup on Amazon, and instrumenting a production environment for further improvement. The Meetup will be directed by Jimmie Butler, a co-founder at Utu Intelligence, a company that is building a bot analytics plat